<item>
            <title>[LU-9899] Lustre test suites need a client on the MGS when MGS on separate node from MDS</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9899</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running testing on a Lustre configuration with a separate MGS and MDS, we need to mount the file system on the MGS so that the lctl command can look in /proc/fs/lustre/*/lov/pools to get the current state of OST pools. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need modify several test scripts or individual tests to mount the file system on the MGS. Tests that manipulate OST pools are:&lt;br/&gt;
sanity: 27D, 200, 253, 406&lt;br/&gt;
replay-single: 85b&lt;br/&gt;
conf-sanity: 82b, 103&lt;br/&gt;
ost_pools: All tests&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Logs for the master patch review test sessions when run against a Lustre file system with separate MGS and MDS are at&lt;br/&gt;
review-zfs-part-1 - &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/a301d35c-6b13-4ec5-8258-01c7512a8b92&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/a301d35c-6b13-4ec5-8258-01c7512a8b92&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
